</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="400">3. Generating multiple credit notes</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you want to generate multiple credit notes at a time, use the search filter in the <strong>Orders » Fulfilment</strong> menu to determine the orders for which credit notes should be generated. In addition, you can determine whether a status change should take place after the credit notes have been generated.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Generating multiple credit notes:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Orders » Fulfilment » Create credit notes / adjustment forms</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings according to <a href="#table-settings-fulfillment-credit-notes">Table 2</a>.<br>
<em>Note</em> that the settings comprise <strong>Search filters</strong> as well as <strong>Procedures</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>gear-wheel</strong> (<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-cog  "></i></span>) to generate the credit notes.<br>
→ A <strong>PDF file</strong> containing the credit notes for the previously selected orders opens.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
